<br>
When you read your Bible and it says one thing, then other people say something completely different... of course I think they are wrong.  It isn't that I am right, it is that they are wrong.  I know it sounds like I am playing the symantics game... but I'm not.  It is possible that I am wrong about somethings, but the things that have been discussed here are right in the bible. <br>
<br>
When you know the truth everything else is a lie.<br>
<br>
No, God does not speak directly to people today.  Not out loud, not in their heads, ONLY through His Word.<br>
<br>
Yes, you did misunderstand, or more possibly I misrepresented myself.  Either way I know God fills many images and roles.  My point was that we are not on equal terms with God and therefor he can not be compared to a lover.  Look at the roles you list.  The shepherd watches the sheep, but also has authority over them.  Father loves his children, but still has authority over them.  Does not meen that a father or a shepherd does not care for those he watches over. <br>
<br>
Lastly, I wasn't attacking Lukaria.  I was talking about the long line of people who state things contrary to scripture.  If I had any memory I would be able to list them without the work of looking them up.  Gonna make a web page instead.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<font color=yellow>Rittdabard,</font color><br>
<br>
All going to hell.  None have done what God asks in scripture.  Now, if you have examples that include people who were immersed in water for the forgiveness of sins....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<font color=yellow>Taun,</font color><br>
<br>
If you saw heaven I am sure you would change your mind.  If your relationship with other created beings can be so great then how much better can the relationship be with the creator?<br>
<br>
I know you don't agree, but you don't have to.  You just have to decide if you like that idea better than the idea of a hot lonely place.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<font color=yellow>Lurikeen,</font color><br>
<br>
Judgement of others is not a fine line, its an easy thing to determine.  If God says don't __________ and the person decides to ________ they are a sinner (as all people are).  Now if they are in Christ they are forgiven.  If, however, they do it on a scheduled basis, knowing ahead of time they are doing wrong and not caring... then they can not be forgiven until they make a change in their life.<br>
<br>
If a guy moves in with his girlfriend and she gets pregnant.  No judgement needed, he is sinning.  He needs to move out.<br>
<br>
<br>
