<br>
Cendan, what if you are wrong in your interpretation of the moral strictures of the Bible and that judging is an abhorrent sin to your God? I am sure you recall &quot;Judge not unless you be judged&quot;? You see the problem is twofold; one of interpretation and what you *think* God is saying to everyone based upon that interpretation.<br>
<br>
So, using your example, if God says ____, and you fail to do ____, then you are a &quot;sinner&quot;. But how do you know that God said anything at all? You say, the Bible is his written word. That you have faith in that written record. But what makes your interpretation any closer to the actual words spoken by god than any other denomination's interpretation? Also, are you considering the textual bumps that go with the Bible where scribes have changed passages, translation problems from dead languages to current languages; and the fact that none of the original texts exist so there is no hope of being 100% certain that todays translations are exact copies of the Words of God? BTW, wouldn't you want that sort of certainty if your eternal soul is on the line? <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>
Necromancer <BR>
