<br>
Here is something that Christians disagree on.  Some say immersion some just get sprinkled.  Since you specified &quot;immersion&quot; then you must think that the sprinkling doesn't count?<br>
<br>
Yes, in the Bible they were actually in the water.  I just don't think it is fair to tell someone they are &quot;saved&quot; or a Christian because they weren't immersed but were sprinkled.  In my opinion, baptism is symbolism for accepting God and Jesus and asking to be forgiven for your sins.  If your church doesn't happen to have a bathtub, I don't think you aren't a Christian.<br>
<br>
